<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="52" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,415,1120,1146]" box="[151,415,1120,1146]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,415,1120,1146]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,415,1120,1146]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
The 
<taxonomicName box="[207,332,1120,1146]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Mesorhaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lacrymans">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[207,332,1120,1146]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">lacrymans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1195,1581]" box="[151,637,1195,1221]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
The 
<taxonomicName box="[203,325,1195,1220]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Mesorhaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lacrymans">
<emphasis box="[203,325,1195,1220]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">lacrymans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group is characterized by:
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="52" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1195,1581]" box="[151,804,1235,1261]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<number box="[151,166,1235,1261]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" value="1.0">1</number>
First flagellomere subrectangular with dorsal arista.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1195,1581]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<number box="[151,166,1275,1301]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" value="2.0">2</number>
Vein M with an almost right angle bend between dm-cu crossvein and apex (
<figureCitation box="[1096,1163,1275,1301]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,255,1752,1776]" captionTargetBox="[266,1333,194,1711]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[249,1344,184,1732]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 1. Mesorhaga lacrymans Parent: a. hypopygium, left lateral. b. male distal tarsus I, dorsal. c. male wing, dorsal. M. cocori n. sp.: d. hypopygium, left lateral. M. sarukhani n. sp.: e. hypopygium, left lateral. M. funebris Parent: f. hypopygium, left lateral. M. hule n. sp.: g. hypopygium, left lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175600/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
Fig. 
<number box="[1151,1163,1275,1301]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
c). 
<specimenCount box="[151,270,1315,1341]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" type="male">
<number box="[151,166,1315,1341]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" value="3.0">3</number>
Males
</specimenCount>
and females often with large area of brown infuscation on wing (
<figureCitation box="[1034,1100,1315,1341]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,255,1752,1776]" captionTargetBox="[266,1333,194,1711]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[249,1344,184,1732]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 1. Mesorhaga lacrymans Parent: a. hypopygium, left lateral. b. male distal tarsus I, dorsal. c. male wing, dorsal. M. cocori n. sp.: d. hypopygium, left lateral. M. sarukhani n. sp.: e. hypopygium, left lateral. M. funebris Parent: f. hypopygium, left lateral. M. hule n. sp.: g. hypopygium, left lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175600/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
Fig. 
<number box="[1088,1100,1315,1341]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
c), although sometimes faint or appearing smoky.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1195,1581]" box="[151,626,1395,1421]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<specimenCount box="[151,270,1395,1421]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" type="male">
<number box="[151,166,1395,1421]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" value="4.0">4</number>
Males
</specimenCount>
sometimes with black halters.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1195,1581]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
The 
<taxonomicName box="[253,375,1435,1460]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Mesorhaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lacrymans">
<emphasis box="[253,375,1435,1460]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">lacrymans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group comprises four Neotropical species occurring in forests (lowlands to elevations of 
<quantity box="[151,242,1475,1501]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" unit="m" value="2000.0">2000 m</quantity>
) along the Cordillera, and includes 
<taxonomicName box="[669,831,1475,1500]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Mesorhaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lacrymans">
<emphasis box="[669,831,1475,1500]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">M. lacrymans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[848,979,1475,1501]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1038,1136,1475,1501]" name="Panama" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Panama</collectingCountry>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[1156,1271,1475,1500]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Mesorhaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cocori">
<emphasis box="[1156,1271,1475,1500]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">M. cocori</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[1288,1423,1475,1501]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[151,243,1515,1540]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Mesorhaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hule">
<emphasis box="[151,243,1515,1540]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">M. hule</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[262,399,1515,1541]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[422,582,1515,1540]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Mesorhaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sarukhani">
<emphasis box="[422,582,1515,1540]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">M. sarukhani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[600,737,1515,1541]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
), and 
<taxonomicName box="[813,951,1515,1540]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Mesorhaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="funebris">
<emphasis box="[813,951,1515,1540]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">M. funebris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[970,1028,1515,1541]" name="Peru" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Peru</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1043,1141,1515,1541]" name="Ecuador" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1204,1330,1515,1541]" name="Venezuela" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
). All are treated below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
